<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — the public presentation</h2>
  <p class="sub">The format you committed to in Block 8 sets your path. All paths put you in front of an audience for the Communication score.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can present my neighbourhood redesign to a public audience, field their questions, and keep the trade-off visible throughout.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Live public activity (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Run your station. Put the choice to visitors, let them weigh it, then show what your plan chose and what it cost. Field questions in plain language, and resist the urge to smooth the trade-off away when someone pushes. Mr. Ignash captures the performance for the rubric.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo or pair · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pre-recorded video + peer-feedback role (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">For students whose video activity was pre-approved and recorded. Submit it at the start of class, then take a structured peer-feedback role at someone else's live station: watch for whether their trade-off stays visible, and give one specific suggestion.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo + group · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Observer warm-up before your turn (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If a public station makes you nervous, observe one other station for about 15 minutes first. Note what makes visitors actually engage with the choice rather than just nod, then bring that into your own.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Finalisation safety-net (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If a deliverable is not ready, or the public format does not work for you, come find Mr. Ignash. The non-public fallback is a 1:1 presentation of the same plan with the same trade-off bar, assessed identically, with nothing posted.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Safety-net</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

